{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958061301/1175.xml":{"full_text":"Friday, june 13, 1958\nCLASSIFIED\n.ADVERTISING.\nADVERTISING IN THESE COLUMNS COSTS THREE CENTS PER\nWORD, FIRST INSERTION; ALL INSERTIONS AFTER FIRST, TWO\nCENTS PER WORD. MINIMUM CHARGE IS 50 CENTS. IF YOU\nWANT TO BUY, RENT, SELL, SWAP, GET A JOB, HIRE HELP,\nFIND SOMETHING LOST, THE CLASSIFIEDS OFFER AN EFFEC\nTIVE AND ECONOMICAL MEDIUM.\nVisit ANDERSON\u2019S SUPER\nMARKET-BEACH STORE at\ntwo mile post. Vacation headquar\nters. Open year \u2019round. Write\nBILL ANDERSON\u2019S RENTAL\nAGENCY, KITTY HAWK, reser\nvations, oceanfront housekeeping\ncottages. T-4-8-tfc\nHOME IMPROVEMENTS\u2014Roof\ning, siding, garages built, rooms\nadded, baths installed complete,\nbrick and cement work, painting\n.r anything else you want to im\nprove your home. Pay nothing\ndown, 36 months to pay. See\nCharles Haskett or phone 5704\nElizabeth City. T-8-9-tfc\nOFFICE SUPPLIES, PRINTING\norders for printing of all kinds\nfilled promptly. We print forms,\nblanks, letterheads, statements, en\nvelopes. Order from your Pilot- and\nHerald Agent, or Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C. We carry book\nkeeping supplies, and some office\nfurniture.\nINDEPENDENT insurance agen\ncies can and will \u201cserve you\nfirst.\u201d Contact us for yours now.\nHugh Fortescue, Washington.\nTPH-8-29-tfc\nCAMELLIAS, azaleas, noilies, va\nriety of evergreen plants 1.00\nup; Pyracantha (red berried);\nnice flowering trees and shrubs;\nJuniper, Cypress, Arborvitae; Let\nus help you to make your home\nmore beautiful. Roanoke Island\nGardens, Manteo, N. C. Corner\nMother Vineyard Rd. T-l-24-tfc\nFOR SALE. Gas space heater, $lO.\nGas 2 Burner Stove, $lO. Gas 4\nburner stove and oven, S2O. Com\nplete beds, double and single, $lO\nChina cabinet, $lO. Frigidaire,\n$lO. Day bed, $lO. Call Mrs.\nO\u2019Neal, Manteo iB7 W-l.\nT-5-30-3tp\nHELP WANTED, male: Man to\nsell Nationally Advertised Wat\nkins products in Hyde County.\nProducts well known for 90 years,\nj Dealers enjoying substantial in\ncrease in come this year. Appli\ncant must have good character and\nown car. If interested write Mr.\nR. L. Rollins, P. O. Box 113, Golds\nboro, N. C. PH-5-29-3tc\nSEASHORE VACATIONS on Hat\nteras Island near Oregon Inlet,\nat low cost family-style boarding.\nPhone 130, Mirlo Beach Lodge, Ro\ndanthe. Write for information.\nARTIFICIAL BREEDING of your\ncows to purebred, proven stocks\nis both profitable and economical.\nThis service available to family\ncow owners, beef producers, dairy\nt herds. All dairy and beef breeds\navailable. Call H. E. Clayton, Bel\nhaven WH 3-3206. P-10-4-tfc\nSAVE YOUR FLOORS and nice\ntile; use plastic and rubber cups\nunder your desk and furniture legs.\nAll sizes in stock. Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C.\nFor your insurance needs see\nW, R. PEARCE, Manteo, N. C.\nAll kinds of insurance\nFOR SALE: At Buxton, ocean\nfront cottage, 7-bedroom, 2\nbaths, central heating plant.\nEquipped for year-round living. E.\ni\u00bb E. Meekins, realtor, phone Kill\nDevil Hills 2911. T-6-13-3tc\nPETUNIAS. Salvia, 1.50 doz;\nSweet William SI.OO Doz.;\nDouble Petunias, Ageratums, Bro\nwallias, $2.00 Doz. Verbena,\nColeus, Lantana, Saltana, 25/ each;\nalso, geraniums, begonias, fuchias,\nachyranthus. ivies, foliage plants,\netc. Roanoke Island Gardens,\nPhone 210-J, Manteo, N. C.\nT-5-9-6tc\nWANTED AT ONCE\u2014Rawleigh\nDealer in Hyde and Tyrrell Coun\nties. Write Rawleigh\u2019s, Dept. NCF-\n480-R, Richmond, Va.\nPH-6-5-4tp\nWANTED \u2014Man with car between\nthe ages of 25 to 55 to handle\na Watkins Business Business in\nHyde County. Dealer willing to\ninvest 5 days a week in handling\nhis own business can make above\naverage earnings. Products Na\ntionally Advertised. Field help\nprovided. Free Insurahce. Com\npany now celebrating 90th year\nin business with great dividend\ndeals. Business is permanent and\nI profitable with no layoffs for the\nI man who wants to operate his\nI own business with Company capi\ntal. For full particulars write to\nday to The J. R. Watkins Com\npany, P. O. Box 5071, Richmond,\nVirginia. PH-5-15-stc\nSAVE NOW on Mattresses. We\nwill allow you $24.50 for any oil\nmattress on the purchase of a new\n$59.50 Dreamer Superior. You pay\nj only $35.00 Old mattresses made\nI new. All new furniture price.\nWe deliver. Weldon Mattress Co.,\nWeldon, N. C. TS-SO-tlte\nCO2 fire extinguishers, S2O each\nor two for $35. USCG approved.\nG. G. Bonner, General Supply Co.,\nManteo. Tel. 4-W. T-11-8-tfc\nTHE OLD SEA CAPTAIN AND\nDRUMMER Book sl, postpaid.\nGet this racy book of dialogue\nfrom Cape Hatteras and the N. C.\nCoastland. Send it to your friends, j\n6 copies $5 postpaid. Times Print\ning Co.. Inc., Manteo, N. C.\nGET-WELL CARDS See our\nnew assortments, just arrived, both\nserious and humorous. TIMES\nPRINTING COMPANY, Manteo.\nREAL ESTATE on Coast. If in-\nterested in buying or selling\nCoastal property of any kind, try\nthe MIRLO CO., Phone 244, Man-\nteo, N. C.\nRUBBER STAMPS made to order,\nstamp pads, etc. Leave orders at\nPilot and Herald Office, in Bel\nhaven or Swan Quarter.\nARTISTS SUPPLIES. Speed ball\nsets, India ink, black drawing\nink, silver ink, white ink, drawing\npaper. TIMES PRINTING CO.,\nInc.. Majiteo. tc\nFOR SALE: Westinghouse table\ntype sewing machine, SSO. Excel\nlent condition. Mrs. Shirley Jor\ndan. Call Manteo 320-J.\nT-5-23-tfc\nFOR SALE Gas refrigerator,\nfamily size. Good working con\ndition. Manteo 196. T-5-30-tfc\nLAWN MOWER REPAIRING. We\nrepair all makes of lawnmowers\nand small gasoline engines. Parts\navailable for all makes and models.\nSatisfaction guaranteed. ALEX\u2019S\nREPAIR SHOP, Wanchese, N. C.\nPhone 248-J2. T-5-2-tfc\nBOAT FOR SALE: 14-ft. Scotch\nCraft boat, 16 hp Scott Atwater\nmotor and Co<x Trailer. Boat newly\npainted and fibre-glassed. $425\ncomplete. Tel. Nags Head 2502 or\ncan be seen at Britt\u2019s Antique\nShop, Nags Head. T-6-6-2tc\nHOUSE FOR RENT: three bed\nrooms, bath, unfurnished. Con\ntact C. B. Parker, Manteo. Tel.\n78-J. T-6-6-2tp\nNET SKIFF, Juniper; copper\nfastened; 25% ft. long; 7 ft.\nwide; in daily use and good repair;\nmay be seen at Fisherman\u2019s Ex\nchange, Stumpy Point, N. S.\nSee R. D. Wise. T-6-13-3tp\nFOR SALE: Norge electric refrig\nerator, 60 lb. freezer chest.\nEdna J. Etheridge. Call Nags\nHead 8151. T-6-6-2tc\nFOR SALE: Best model gas equip\nment at reasonable prices. 1\napartment model 20-inch Tappan\nstove, 4 burners with oven and\nseparate broiler with pilot lights,\nlike new. 2 white enamel Perfec\ntion automatic hot water heaters,\nonly slightly used. Both in perfect\nworking order, one 40 gallons, one\n30 gallons. Call Kitty Hawk 2061.\nT-6-13-tfc\nFOR SALE: 64 acres, Nags Head\nWoods, 941 ft. Sound frontage.\nThis is a landscape architect\u2019s\ndream. E. E. Meekins, realtor,\nphone Kill Devil Hills 2911.\nT-6-13-3tc\nFOR SALE: MASHOES, Dare\nmainland, 17 acres, 1 2-bedroom\nhouse, 700 feet water frontage. E.\nE. Meekins, realtor, Phone Kill\nDevil Hills 2911. T-6-13-3tc\nFOR SALE: 2-bedroom brick home\nin Manteo, unfurnished. E. E.\nMeekins, realtor, phone Kill Devil\nHills 2911. T-6-13-3tc\nFOR SALE: Cottage court at\nNags Head, west side, 7 units.\nE. E. Meekins, realtor, phone Kill\nDevil Hills 2911. T-6-13-3tc\nT-6-13-3tc\nMAN OR WOMAN\u2014Established\nWatkins Route available in Bel\nhaven, no experience necessary in\nthis area. Write the J. R. Watkins\nCo., P. O. Box 5071, Richmond,\nVa. PH-6-12-4tp\nCARD OF THANKS\nI wish to take this opportunity\nto thank everyohe who brightened\nmy days in the Albemarle Hos\npital with their visits, cards and\nflowers. Your thoughtfulness is\nreally appreciated.\nMARY MANN EVANS\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of John Alford\nFarrow of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said John Alford\nFarrow to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will be\nnleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment\nThis the sth dav of May. 1958.\nALICE F. MEEKINS\nAvon, N. C.\nT-5-9-\u00abte\nilk\nMEEKINS\nSTANDING AT\nTHE CROSSROADS\nThe principal part of the income\nof the people of the coastland is\nderived today from the money that\npeople bring here to spend in the\npursuit of fish and other sports,\nand the enjoyment of our fresh\nair, fine scenery and superb sea\nshore.\nMany of these people are well\noff in the general term, and they\nhave money to spend because they\nwere smart enough to earn it. Be\ncause they knew how to get it in\nthe highly competitive world in\nwhich some of us don\u2019t have to\nstruggle, we must assume they are\nsmart enough to keep others from\ntaking it away from them if they\ndon\u2019t want it taken.\nThey have the human instincts\nof friendliness and .perception, and\noft-times they contribute liberally\nto such worthy causes as appeal to\ntheir fancy, but they are dangerous\nand, hard to handle when they be\nlieve they are being taken for a\nride.\nStrongly imbedded in the\nmaxims that have contrived to\nbuild America\u2019s greatness is this\none: \u201cMillions for defense, but not\none cent for tribute.\u201d\n.The inscription now engraved on\ngranite in a Charleston cemetery\nis attributed to Charles Coatsworth\nPinckney, our minister to the\nFrench Republic in 1797. Good\nauthority has it that he really\nsaid: \u201cnot a damned penny for\ntribute.\u201d\nWe might well bear this in mind\nin all our dealings with those peo\nple on whom our livelihood de\npends. Now let us analyze the\nsituation.\nOur property long laying waste\nhas been developed and bought by\nstrangers at prices which caused\nthem to be laughed at when it\nbegan 30 years ago.\nThis property has been built up\nuntil it reasonably constitutes half\nthe wealth of the coastland. These\npeople have made valuable and\nbeneficial contributions to all\nof us, something with which we\ncould do nothing ourselves.\nA few modest fortunes among\nour natives or other residents have\nbeen founded in a short time by\nthose who through good fortune or\nforesight happened to get for a\nsong, a piece of wasteland and sold\nit at fabulous prices.\nIt was our good fortune indeed\nthat providence favored us with\ngreat history, scenery and climate,\nand an oceanside unmatched any\nwhere in America.\nLike all of nature\u2019s bounties,\nsuch as good fortune, good health,\nand true friends, it deserves every\nprotection and consideration.\nTranslated into conservation it\nwill continue to be a source of\nwealth, yielding oui- livelihood for\ngeneration after generation of our\npeople.\nIn dealing with i the newcomers\nwho have done so much for us, it\nmight be well for us to consider\nhow much we will do for them in\nreturn.\nAs non-residents now pay over\nhalf the taxes received by Dare\nCounty, it doesn\u2019t appear com\nmonsense to try to force mthem to\npay nine-tenths of our income, as\nsome officials would willingly do.\nIf we be fair and just we must\nremember that these people spend\nonly a small part of the year in\nour county. Seashore property is\nsubject to greater wear and tear,\nand inroads from the weather. Left\nalone and unprotected with a bare\ntoken policing by officials, it is\ncostly to maintain.\nOwners of this property are first\nto pay their taxes; mostly all pay\non receipt of the first statement\nOperating on this early income, the\ncounty therefore is able to be more\nlenient on the average citizen of\nthe county; even some public offi\ncials don\u2019t pay their taxes before\nadvertising date.\nNow all the people of our\ncoastland share in benefits from\nthis money paid on property de\nveloped by newcomers who stay\nhere only a small part of the year.\nThey do not share in th6 bene\nfits of our schools, and bling ,no\nincrease to enrollment to make\nextra cost.\nThey add no burdens on our\nwelfare department whose bounty\nfor many years at a cost greater\nthan the sum we have paid for\neducation, goes for the benefit of\nnative residents only.\nThey bring no increased costs to\nour courthouse or persons to be\nfed in our jail, and those who are\nbrought into court for highway in\nfractions, pay off in cash to the\ntune of 15 to 20 thousand dollars a\nyear for the benefit of our school\nfunds.\nThis sort of newcomer is the\nfinest type of visitor for counties\nwith seashore property like Dare,\nHyde and Currituck, so therefore\nit seems not out of order to find\nsome way to give him part of his\nmoney back in the form of serv\nices or other consideration.\nIt would be a terrific loss if such\nTHE COASTI.AND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\npeople stopped coming to invest in\nproperty and to stop spending\namong our business houses and\nworking men.\nRecent developments have\nbrought us to a halt in our rapid\nstrides of the past few years, and\nwe are standing at a cross roads\nwhere it is necessary to take\nthought.\nConsidered decision is necessary\nbefore deciding the way to go.\nFOR SALE. Maytag washer,\nMrs. Mildred Austin. Phone 212-J\nManteo.\nT-6-13-2tc\nIN MEMORY\nIn Loving Memory of Esther D.\nForbes (Poll) who died two years\nago\u2014June 11, 1956.\nTwo years have passed dear loved\none\nsince you left us here to moan,\nbut we believe you are with Jeeus\nin that bright and happy home.\nWe still miss you so much\nas the family gathers here.\nWe always seem to hear your voice\nto see your smile so dear.\nWhat happy hours we once\nenjoyed,\nhow sweet their memory still,\nbut they have left an aching void\nthe world can never fill.\nBut we\u2019re so glad that Jesus\npromises,\nif we will only live for him,\nwe can all be re-united\nin that world that knows no end.\nSigned:\nMother, Husband children,\nsisters and brothers\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nNotice is hereby given tlrtt the\npartnership heretofore existing\nwherein Dan C. Morrill and Char\nlotte S. Morrill were partners trad\ning and doing business under the\nfirm name of Island Photo Service,\nin the Town of Manteo, in the\nCounty of Dare, North Carolina,\nhas this day been dissolved by\nmutual consent of the partners.\nThis 16th day of May, 1958.\n/s/ DAN C. MORRILL\n/s/ CHARLOTTE S.' MORRILL\nT-5-30-4tc\nNOTICE OF SALE\nSTATE OF NORTH CAROLINA\nCOUNTY OF DARE\nUnder and by virtue of the\npower of sale contained in a cer\ntain deed of trust executed by El\nmer V. Midgett and Evelyn Mid\ngett, his wife, dated the 20th day of\nMarch, 1956 and recorded in Book\nNo. 66 on page 252 in the office\nof the Register of Deeds, Dare\nCounty, North Carolina, default\nhaving been made in the payment\nof the indebtedness thereby secur\ned and the said deed of trust being\nby its terms subject to trustee\u2019s\nforeclosure sale, the undersigned\ntrustee will offer for sale at pub\nlic auction to highest bidder for\ncash at the Courthouse door, Man\nteo. N. C., being sold at 12 o\u2019clock\nnoon on the 20 day of June, 1958,\nthe following described property:\nA parcel of land described as\nParcel B of tract No. six in that\ncertain Report of Commissioners\nin a partition proceeding dated\nJune 22, 1951, and duly recorded\nin Book 41, page 209, Office of\nthe Register of Deeds, Dare\nCounty. North Carolina, map or\nplat showing said parcel record\ned with the proceedings. Said\nportion of Parcel B. being de\nscribed as:\nBeginning at a stake or other\nmarker, said beginning point be\ning South 76 degrees 30 minutes\nEast a distance of 400 feet from\nan iron axel located on the east\nern margin of the right-of-way\nof that highway known as the\nHatteras Highway which extends\nfrom Oregon Inlet to the village\nof Hatteras; said irort axel here\nin referred to as a reference\npoint being in the south line of\nParcel B of Tract No. 6, as said\nsouth line intersects with the\naforesaid right-ofway, same be\ning shown on the map or plat\nhereinabove mentioned; and run\nning thence from said beginning\npoint in a northerly direction and\nparallel with aforesaid highway\nright-of-way a distance of 68.1\nfeet to a stake or other marker;\nand running thence South 76\ndegrees 30 minutes East along\nthe northern line of the Parcel\nB of Tract No. 6 as shown on\naforesaid map a distance of 1900\nfeet more or less to the high\nwater mark of the Atlantic\nOcean; and thence running in a\nsoutherly direction along the\nhighwater mark of the Atlantic\nOcean a distance of 68.1 feet;\nand thence running North 76\ndegrees 30 minutes West along\nthe southern line of Parcel B of\nTract No. 6 as shown on afore\nsaid map a distance of 1900 feet\nmore or less to the stake or\nother marker at the place of\nbeginning.\nAnd being the portion of Par\ncel B of Tract No. 6 which lies\nbetween a line parallel with and\n400 feet distance from the afore\nsaid highway right-of-way, and\nthe highwater mark of the At\nlantic Ocean.\nTerms of sale: Cash, or such\nother terms as the Trustee may\ndeed expedient.\nThe property is to be sold as\nis, yyhere is, without warranty of\nany kind, and subject to taxes\nand/or assessments, if any.\nPurchaser will not be allowed\nto sever or remove any of the\nsaid property or to take possession\nthereof without first complying\nwith the bid.\nDated this 16 day of May, 1958.\nCLARENCE P. MOORE, Trustee\nT-5-23-4tc\nNORTH CAROLINA I\nDARE COUNTY\nNOTICE OF SALE\nUnder and by virtue of the\npower of sale contained in a cer\ntain deed of trust executed by\nRobert H. Parker and wife, Elsie\nD. Parker, dated the 2nd day of\nApril, 1953, and recorded in Book\n43, page 457, in the office of the\nRegister of Deeds of Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, default having\nbeen made with respect to compli\nance with the terras of said deed\nof trust and said deed of trust\nbeing by the terms thereof subject\nto foreclosure, the undersigned\nTrustee will offer for sale at pub\nlic auction to the highest bidder\nfor cash at the courthouse door\nin Manteo, North Carolina, at\nNoon, on the 10th day of July,\n1958, the propel ty conveyed in\nsaid deed of trust, the same lying\nand being in the County of Dare\nand State of North Carolina, in\nAtlantic Township, and more par\nticularly described as follows:\nAll those certain tracts or par\ncels of land, together with the\nhouses and improvements there\non, lying and being in Atlantic\nTownship, Dare County, N. C.,\nand more particularly described\nas follows:\nFIRST TRACT: Those certain\ntracts or parcels of land in Dare\nCounty, N. C., known and\ndelineated on the map of Kitty\nHawk Beach Subdivision which\nmap is recorded in Book 13,\npage 440, now recorded in Map\nBook 1, page 194, Public Reg\nistry of Dare County, N. C., as\nLots No. 1,2, 3,4, 5 and 6 in\nBlock 63, reference to which is\nhereby made for a more com\nplete description of said lands.\nExcepting, however, from the\nabove described lands and this\nconveyance, that certain parcel\nof land conveyed by James E.\nGarrett et ux to Paul W. Elam,\net al, by deed dated November\n5, 1949 and recorded in Book 36.\npage 311, office of the Register\nof Deeds of Dare County, N. C.,\nreference to which is hereby\nmade for a more particular de\nscription thereof.\nSECOND TRACT: That cer\ntain tract of land in Dare\nCounty, N. C, which begins in\nthe Southern line of the high\nway sometimes known as Vir\nginia Dare Trail, or a projection\nthereof, at a point 50 feet West\nerly from the Northwest corner\nof Lot No. 1, Block 63, on the\nmap aforesaid, and runs South\nerly parallel to and 50 feet from\nthe Western line of said Lot\nNo. 1200 feet; thence in a\nstraight line the same course as\nthe Virginia Dare Trail to Cur\nrituck Sound; thence Northwest\nerly with Currituck Sound 200\nfeet, and to a point where said\nSound would be intersected by\nthe Southern line of Virginia\nDare Trail, if projected to the\nSound; thence Eastwardly in a\nstraight line to the place of be\nginning. Reference is hereby had\nand directed to the map or plat\nabove mentioned for a more\ncomplete and detailed descrip\ntion.\nTHIRD TRACT: All riparian\nrights in Currituck Sound to\nwhich the vendees would be en\ntitled by virtue of their owner\nship of the land hereby conveyed\nmay at any time hereafter be\nconsidered.\nSame being the lands conveyed'\nto James E. Garrett et ux by\nW. E. Garrett, Jr., and wife,\nAnnis R. Garrett, by deed dated\nJune 5, 1916 and duly recorded\nin Book 29, page 597, office of\nthe Register of Deeds of Dare\nCounty, N. C.\nThere is also conveyed hereby\nall furniture, fixtures and equip\nment in the buildings and located\non the above described lands and\npremises, including, but not\nlimited to, the following articles:\nI Magic Chef Gas Stove\n1 Oil Stove\nI Rudd Gas Water Heater\nAll cooking utensils\n1 Gould Electric Water Pump\n2 Row Boats\n1 8 foot Drink Cooler\n1 Victor Deep Freeze Box\nSame being the lands conveyed\nto Robert H. Parker et ux by\nJames E. Garrett et ux by deed\ndated April 2, 1953 and duly\nfiled for record in the office of\nthe Register of Deeds of Dare\nCounty, North Carolina.\nThe persons or person making\nthe last and highest bid will be\nrequired to make a cash deposit\nin the amount of ten percent of\nthe first $1,000.00 bid and five per\ncent of all over $1,000.00 bid.\nThis sale will be made subject\nto all outstanding and unpaid\nand <\u2019necinl assessments.\nThis 9th day of June, 1958.\nMartin Kellogg, Jr.\nTRUSTEE\nBY: FRANK B. AYCOCK, Jr.\nAttorney for Trustee\nT-6-13-4t\nRESERVE I\nMl $2.50\nPint\nfSchinleu\nI\nI\nBLENDED WHISKY, 86 PROOF, 65* GRAIN\nNEUTRAL SPIRITS, SCHENLEY DIST.,N.Y.Q.\nBUS SCHEDULE\nBETWEEN MANTEO\nAND HATTERAS\nEffective April 1, 1958\nNORTHBOUND\nLv. Hatteras 9:00 A.M.\nAr. Manteo 11:45 A.M.\nSOUTHBOUND\nLv. Manteo 2:45 P.M.\nAr. Hatteras 5:45 P.M.\nCHARTERED TRIPS\nHATTERAS-MANTEp\nBUS LINE\nPhone 104 Hatteras, N. C.\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Dennett Hen\nry Ransom of Frisco, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Dennett Henry\nRansom to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will\nbe pleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAH persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 28th day of April, 1958.\nELLA MAY RANSOM\nFrisco, N. C.\nT-5-2-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executors\nof the Estate of Guy H. Lennon,\nof Dare County, North Carolina,'\nthis is to notify all persons hav-!\ning claims against the Estate of\nsaid Guy H. Lennon, to present I\nthem to the undersigned within I\none year from the date of this\nnotice, or the same will be pleaded\nin bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said\nEstate please make immediate\npayment to the undersigned.\nThis 4th day of June, 1958\nR. B. LENNON\nW. E. LENNON, M. D.\nExecutors\nMcCown McCown, Attorneys\nManteo, N. C.\nT-6-6-6tc\nNOTICE TO BIDDERS\nFOR THE REMOVAL OF>\nGARBAGE AND TRASH\nON THE DARE BEACHES\nSealed bids will be received in the office of the\nRegister of Deeds, as Clerk to the Board of County Com\nmissioners of Dare County, until 12:00 o'clock Noon on\nJune 17, 1958 for the removal of all garbage and house\nhold trash, exclusive of construction materials, from the\nportion of the Dare Beaches described hereinafter for the\nperiod beginning July I, 1958 and terminating June 30,\n1959, in accordance with the following schedule:\nCollections are to be made once each day, except\nSundays, during the period beginning July I, 1958'\nthrough September 30, 1958 inclusive, and twice each\nweek during the period from October I, 1958 to and in\ncluding the 15th day of May, 1959, and three times each\nweek during the period from the 16th day of May, 1959\nto and including the 31st day of May, 1959, and once each\nday, except Sundays, for the period from June I, 1959\nthrough June 30, 1959 inclusive.\nThe general territory and area from which the afore\nsaid household trash and garbage shall be removed in\ncludes all houses, hotels, places of business and restaurants\nlying adjacent to and in the vicinity of and along that,\nsection of the present U. S. Highway No. 158 extending;\nfrom the East end of the Currituck Sound Bridge to the\nEast end of the Roanoke Sound Bridge, the entire South\nern Shores road or street leading North from U. S. High\nway No. 158, including the area or subdivision in Southern\nShores known as Crescent Village, that portion of the\nOregon Inlet road leading South from the aforesaid High\nway No. 158 lying North of the Cape Hatteras National\nSeashore Recreational Area's North line, that portion of\nthe Beach known as the Southside at Nags Head and the\npaved road leading thereto, all of the area and subdivi\nsion known as Avalon Beach or Shores, and on both sides\nof any paved or stabilized and all weather road or street\nleading from U. S. Highway No. 158 or U. S. Highway\nNo. 64 now in being, upon which houses have been\nconstructed, for a distance not in excess of one-half mile.\nThe contractor will be required to provide a dumping\nground or other disposal area for the aforesaid trash and\ngarbage which shall not be in violation of any health or\nothefr laws. The contractor will likewise be required to\nfurnish trucks or other disposal units or equipment which\nare covered and enclosed, and which prevents seepage or\nleakage of wet garbage.\nEach bid or proposal shall be accompanied by a\ncash deposit or a certified check or bank draft made\nEayable to the order of Dare County drawn on some\nank or trust company insured by the Federal Deposit\nInsurance Corporation in an amount equal to not less\nthan five percent of the proposal or bid. No proposal\nor bid shall be accepted or considered by the said Board\nunless at the time of its filing the same shall be accom\npanied by said deposit or check as aforesaid. This deposit\nshall be retained by Dare County if the bidder who is\naccepted and to whom the contract is awarded fails to\nexecute the contract for the aforesaid removal of garbage\nand household trash on or before the 26th day of June,\n1958, and fails to give the performance bond as provided\nhereinafter.\nThe successful bidder will be required to give a per\nformance Bond for 100 percent of the contract price\nGuaranteeing the faithful performance of bis contract.\nSaid bond to be executed by a surety company licensed\nunder the laws of the State of North Carolina to execute\nsuch a bond.\nThe right to reject any and all bids and proposals\nfor any reason whatsoever is hereby reserved.\nFurther information concerning the bids and a copy\nof the contract which the accepted bidder will be required\nto enter info may be had at the office of the Register of\nDeeds of Dare County, North Carolina.\nThis the 4th day of June, 1958.\nMELVIN R. DANIELS, CLERK TO THE BOARD OF\nCOUNTY COMMISSIONERS OF DARE COUNTY, N. C.\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned having duly\nqualified as the administrator of\nthe Estate of Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, late of the above named\ncounty and state, all persons hav\ning claims of whatsoever nature\nagainst the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby notified to\nexhibit the said claim or claims to\nthe undersigned on \u00bbr before the\n2nd day of May, 1959, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery. All persons indebt-\nI ed to the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby requested to\npay the said indebtedness to the\nundersigned immediately.\nThis the 2nd day of May, 1958.\nFLOYD L. HOOPER\nAdministrator\nT-5-2-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Naomi D.\nWescott of Manteo, Dare County.:\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Naomi D. Wes\ncott to present them to the under\nsigned within one year from date\nof this notice or same will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 6th day of May, 1958.\nBROCKIIE DANIELS\nManteo, N. C.\nT-5-16-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executor of\nthe estate of Daisy H. Midgett of\nNags Head, Dare County, North\nCarolina, this is to notify all per-\ni sons having claims against the\nI estate of said Daisy H. Midgett,\nto present them to the undersigned\nwithin one year from date of this\nnotice or same will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate please make\nimmediate payment.\nThis the 3rd day of May, 1958.\nCORNELIUS P. MIDGETT\nNags Head, N. C. i\nWorth and Horner, Attorney.\nT-5-9-6tc\nPAGE NINE","height":"25634","width":"18325"}}
